'''Naftiran Intertrade Company S<U+00E0>rl (NICO)''' is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]]-based subsidiary of the [[National Iranian Oil Company]] (NIOC). NICO is a general contractor for the [[oil and gas industry]]. NIOC buys the vast majority of [[National Iranian Oil Refining and Distribution Company#Fuel imports|Iran's gasoline imports]].<ref name="time.com">{{cite news|last=Calabresi |first=Massimo |url=http://www.time.com/time/nation/article/0,8599,1996921,00.html |title=Sleeping with the Enemy: BP's Deals with Iran |publisher=TIME |date=2010-06-16 |accessdate=2012-02-07}}</ref> Naftiran is a key player in [[Energy in Iran|Iran's energy sector]]. Naftiran is a key player in [[Energy in Iran|Iran's energy sector]].<ref name="time.com"/>

NICO also handles [[Trade|trading]] & [[swap (finance)|swap]]s operations on behalf of NIOC. [[Iran]] has swap arrangements with [[Azerbaijan]], [[Turkmenistan]], and [[Kazakhstan]], under which it ships crude from the [[Central Asia]]n producers to its [[Caspian Sea|Caspian]] ports. In exchange Iran delivers the equivalent barrels of crude on behalf of the three Central Asian producers to their costumers in the [[Persian Gulf]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.presstv.com/detail.aspx?id=131131&sectionid=351020103 |title=No Operation |publisher=Presstv.com |date= |accessdate=2012-02-07}}</ref>

==History==
''Naftiran Trading Services (NTS)'' was established in the [[Jersey|Jersey Channel]] Islands (United Kingdom) in 1991. The intention was to start trading crude oil and products, as well as to create a competitive opportunity for the investment in oil and gas projects, as well as to play an active role in world [[energy security]]. In June 2003, a decision was made by NICOs management to transfer the whole NTS activities to a newly established company named Naftiran Intertrade Co ([[Soci<U+00E9>t<U+00E9> <U+00E0> responsabilit<U+00E9> limit<U+00E9>e|S<U+00E0>rl]]), in [[Lausanne]], [[Switzerland]].<ref name=edoceo/><ref name=Naftiran>{{cite web|url=http://naftiran.com/about.aspx |title=NICO Naftiran Intertrade Company - AboutUs |publisher=Naftiran.com |date= |accessdate=2012-07-16}}</ref>

Petro Suisse Intertrade, Hong Kong Intertrade, Noor Energy (Malaysia) and Petro Energy Intertrade, all alleged [[front company|front companies]] for NIOC/NICO, have been [[US sanctions against Iran|sanctioned by the United States]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-18822957 |title=BBC News - US tightens sanctions over Iran nuclear programme |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=2012-07-12 |accessdate=2012-07-16}}</ref>

===Revenues===
From 2005 to 2008, NICO's revenue increased by 50%, from $14.7 billion to $21.9 billion, while its net income rose from $129 million to $134 million.<ref name="time.com"/>

==Subsidiaries==
===Petropars===
Petropars is a general contractor for the oil & gas industry.

===PetroIran===
{{main|PetroIran}}
Petroiran Development Company (aka [[PetroIran]] or PEDCO) is a general offshore contractor. PEDCO was initially formed to be the Iranian partner of foreign contractors with a 10% share in each [[Foreign Direct Investment in Iran#Buy-back|buy-back contract]].

====Participations in foreign gas fields====
*Iran owns 50% of the [[Rhum gasfield|offshore gas field of Rhum]] in the [[North Sea]], which is [[UK|Britain's]] largest untapped gas field. It is a joint-venture with [[British Petroleum|BP]] worth $1 million a day at June 15, 2010 spot prices.<ref name="time.com"/>

*Iran has another 10% joint-venture participation with BP and other foreign oil companies in Azerbaijani [[Shah Deniz gas field]], producing 8 billion cubic meters of gas per year, worth up to a reported $2.4 billion per year.<ref name="time.com"/> Shah Deniz is not subject to [[U.S. sanctions against Iran|US sanctions]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://presstv.com/detail/222661.html |title=BP exempted from US ban on Iran oil |publisher=PressTV |date=2012-01-23 |accessdate=2012-02-07}}</ref>

===Iranian Oil Company (IOC)===
IOC is in charge of [[Rhum gasfield]] in the [[United Kingdom]].

====Foreign participation====
As at 2010, NICO is a shareholder in [[British Petroleum|BP]], holding 24,683,858 shares of the company, worth approximately $775 million, and representing 0.8% of the company's common stock.<ref name="time.com"/>

